<styl>by <m2>By <m0>ALINA MATAS<ql>
<m1><styl>crline <m0>Herald Business Writer<ql>
<m1><ep>
<m0> Perfumania, a Miami perfume retailer, plans to buy the retail division and part of the wholesale operation of competitor Model Imperial in a deal that would give Perfumania 650 more retail outlets and bail out financially troubled Model Imperial.<ep>
  The sale, announced Wednesday, involves two letters of intent. One is for Perfumania to buy all of Boca Raton-based Model Imperial's retail operations. The second is to buy 51 percent of what remains of Model Imperial.<ep>
  The transactions are subject to approval by Model Imperial's lenders (--) who had pressured the company to shrink and pay off a $50 million debt (--) and to final review and audits of Model Imperial's 1995 financial statements, on which the company requested an extension.<ep>
  Model Imperial, solely a wholesaler until 1993, expects losses of more than $20 million for 1995. The company blames its financial woes on the rapid expansion of its retail operation, which grew to 650 leased departments inside other retailers' stores in two years. Model Imperial has been operating <m2><ql>
